Each [relationship object](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-resource-object-relationships) MUST contain at least one of the following: `links`, `data`, or `meta`.

Therefore, this is not allowed:

```
{
  "relationships": {"author": {}, "comments": {}}
}
```

An empty relationships member is not invalid, but kind of silly:

```
{
  "relationships": {}
}
```

The following is valid:

```
{
  "relationships": {"author": {"data": null}, "comments": {"data": []}}
}
```

And so is this:

```
{
  "type": "articles",
  "id": "1",
  "attributes": {
    "title": "Rails is Omakase"
  },
  "relationships": {
    "author": {
      "links": {
        "self": "/articles/1/relationships/author",
        "related": "/articles/1/author"
      },
      "data": { "type": "people", "id": "9" }
    }
  }
}
```

Note that the `data` element above is totally optional. It's not required, except in the case of a compound document.

I fixed it with overriding `clean` method of `CharWidget`:

```python
class CharWidget(widgets.CharWidget):

    def clean(self, value, row=None, *args, **kwargs):
        if isinstance(value, float):
            value = int(value)
            return "{}".format(value)
        return value
```

