If you have django-admin-bootstrapped installed, the latest working version of django-import-export is 0.42.
After upgrade to 0.43 list_filters don't work.
Here is my solution (i don't know if it will work in your case):
Change this file: **_import_export/templates/admin/import_export/change_list.html_**
```
import_export/templates/admin/import_export/change_list.html 

{% extends "admin/change_list.html" %}

{# Original template renders object-tools only when has_add_permission is True. #}
{# This hack allows sub templates to add to object-tools #}
{% block object-tools %}
  <ul class="object-tools">
    {% block object-tools-items %}
      {% if has_add_permission %}
        {{ block.super }}
      {% endif %}
    {% endblock %}
  </ul>
{% endblock %}
```
to
```
{% extends "admin/change_list.html" %}

{# Original template renders object-tools only when has_add_permission is True. #}
{# This hack allows sub templates to add to object-tools #}
{% block object-tools %}{{ block.super }}{% endblock %}
```
It works for me with the latest (0.6.0) version.

